Exception-Handling
- Exception is a event which will  causing a Programm Termination

Types of Exceptions
1) Checked Exceptions
2) Un-Checked Exceptions

1) Checked Exceptions- identify by the compiler
Ex: Interrupted Exception
FileNotFound
IOException

we can handle by
throws
and try catch as well


2) Un-Checked Exceptions -NOT identify by the compiler
- Arithmetic Exception
- InputMismatchException
- NullPointer Exception
- NumberFormat Exception
- ArrayIndexOutOfBoundException --etc


try {
}catch(){
}
finally{

}

case 1- Exception Occured , catch block handles - finally block will execute
case 2 - Exception Occured , catch block NOT  handled - finally block will execute
case 3 - Exception Not Occured , catch block ignored --> finally block will execute

throw      -> Creates and throws an exception.

throws     -> Declares that a method may throw an exception
              and passes the handling responsibility to the caller.

try-catch  -> Handles the exception.

JVM        -> Final handler if nobody catches the exception.
              It terminates the program and prints the stack trace.